                <h1>John Winthrop: Founder of a City Upon a Hill</h1>
                <p>John Winthrop was an English Puritan lawyer and one of the founding figures of the Massachusetts Bay Colony. He served as its governor for many years and envisioned the colony as a "city upon a hill," a model of Christian charity and morality. Winthrop's leadership and writings greatly influenced American political and social thought.</p>
